#: .\modinfo.json
msgid "Bootleg Walkers"
msgstr "山寨步行者"

#. ~ Description for Bootleg Walkers
#: .\modinfo.json
msgid ""
"Allows one to construct shoddy knock-offs of the Northrup ATSV chicken "
"walker.  For more information, consult the README.md file."
msgstr "允许建造诺斯罗普 ATSV 鸡形步行者的劣质仿制品。更多信息，请查阅 README.md 文件。"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "rifle"
msgid_plural "rifles"
msgstr[0] "步枪"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid ""
"The weapon occasionally tries to bite you with its many mouths, when it "
"succeeds it purrs contentedly."
msgstr "这把武器偶尔会用它的许多嘴试图咬你，成功时会满足地发出呼噜声。"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "shotgun"
msgid_plural "shotguns"
msgstr[0] "霰弹枪"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "This weapon spits lead pellets at you whenever you touch its tendrils."
msgstr "每当你触碰它的触须时，这把武器就会向你喷射铅弹。"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "flaregun"
msgid_plural "flareguns"
msgstr[0] "信号枪"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid ""
"This small and toothsome weapon occasionally exhales smoke, and smells of "
"burning magnesium."
msgstr "这把小巧可口的武器偶尔会喷出烟雾，并带有燃烧镁的气味。"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "M2 Browning"
msgid_plural "M2 Brownings"
msgstr[0] "M2 勃朗宁"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid ""
"This weapon almost constantly trembles in rage, and is too large to "
"comfortably hold."
msgstr "这把武器几乎一直在愤怒地颤抖，而且太大，握起来不舒服。"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "blaster"
msgid_plural "blasters"
msgstr[0] "爆能枪"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "This weapon glows in places, and is almost painfully hot to the touch."
msgstr "这把武器在某些部位发光，摸起来几乎烫得难受。"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "laser"
msgid_plural "lasers"
msgstr[0] "激光枪"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid ""
"This weapon's many eyes constantly move, only settling for a mere moment "
"before finding a new focus."
msgstr "这把武器的许多眼睛不断移动，只停留片刻就会找到新的焦点。"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "flamethrower"
msgid_plural "flamethrowers"
msgstr[0] "火焰喷射器"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "This weapon gurgles softly, and occasionally drips burning liquid."
msgstr "这把武器轻轻发出咕噜声，偶尔会滴下燃烧的液体。"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "semi auto"
msgstr "半自动"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "auto"
msgstr "自动"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "slosh."
msgstr "晃动。"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "tesla coil"
msgid_plural "tesla coils"
msgstr[0] "特斯拉线圈"

#: .\walker_gun.json
msgid "Blue-green electricity arcs between this weapons twitching cilia."
msgstr "蓝绿色的电弧在这把武器颤动的纤毛间跳跃。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "Northrup ATSV schematics"
msgid_plural "Northrup ATSV schematics"
msgstr[0] "诺斯罗普ATSV设计图"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Northrup ATSV schematics', 'str_pl': 'Northrup
#. ATSV schematics'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A heavily classified document containing schematics for Northrups ATSV "
"combat walker."
msgstr "一份高度机密的文件，内含诺斯罗普ATSV战斗步行机的设计图。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken chickenbot"
msgid_plural "broken chickenbots"
msgstr[0] "损坏的鸡形机器人"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken chickenbot'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken chicken walker.  Still looks intimidating despite being permanently"
" inoperative, possibly due to the sheer size and mass.  Could be gutted for "
"parts."
msgstr "一台损坏的鸡形步行机。尽管已永久失效，但其庞大的体型和质量仍令人望而生畏。可拆解获取零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "inactive chicken walker"
msgid_plural "inactive chicken walkers"
msgstr[0] "未激活的鸡形步行机"

#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'inactive chicken walker'}.
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "The chicken bot rolls out and begins acquiring targets."
msgstr "鸡形机器人出动并开始锁定目标。"

#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'inactive chicken walker'}.
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"The chicken bot swivels its turret and aims directly at you.  Don your brown"
" pants!"
msgstr "鸡形机器人旋转炮塔并直接瞄准你。快穿上你的棕色裤子！"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'inactive chicken walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"This is an inactive chicken walker.  Using this item involves placing it on "
"the ground, loading the unit with the factory-loaded 5.56 rounds and 40mm "
"cartridge grenades in your inventory (if you wish to divide your ammunition,"
" set aside whatever ammunition you do NOT want to give the robot) and "
"turning it on.  If reprogrammed and rewired successfully the tank drone will"
" then identify you as a friendly, roam around or follow you, and attack all "
"enemies with a built-in firearm and grenade launcher."
msgstr ""
"这是一台未激活的鸡形步行机。使用此物品需将其放置在地面，从库存中为它装载出厂预装的5.56毫米子弹和40毫米榴弹（若想分配弹药，请先预留你不想给机器人的部分），然后启动。若成功重编程并重新接线，坦克无人机会将你识别为友方，四处巡逻或跟随你，并用内置枪械与榴弹发射器攻击所有敌人。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "Pathfinder chassis"
msgid_plural "Pathfinder chassis"
msgstr[0] "探路者底盘"

#. ~ Description for {'str_sp': 'Pathfinder chassis'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"What's left when you remove all moving parts and electronics.  It's the "
"skeleton and armor of the pathfinder."
msgstr "移除所有活动部件和电子设备后的剩余部分。这是探路者的骨架与装甲。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "walker chassis"
msgid_plural "walker chassiss"
msgstr[0] "步行机底盘"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'walker chassis'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An ATSV chassis, hand-forged from scrap.  An integral component for bootleg "
"walkers."
msgstr "一个ATSV底盘，由废料手工锻造而成。是组装山寨步行机的核心部件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "super chassis"
msgid_plural "super chassiss"
msgstr[0] "超级底盘"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'super chassis'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An ATSV chassis, carefully crafted with the best materials and to the "
"highest standards possible in a post-Cataclysm world."
msgstr "一个ATSV底盘，采用后大灾变世界中可能的最佳材料和最高标准精心打造。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed chicken walker"
msgid_plural "packed chicken walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的鸡式步行机"

#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed chicken walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed scrap walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed unarmed walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed bootleg walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed tesla walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed fusion walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed buckshot walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed flare walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed laser walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed flamer walker'}.
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "The walker begins scanning for hostiles."
msgstr "步行机开始扫描敌对目标。"

#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed chicken walker'}.
#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed scrap walker'}.
#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed unarmed walker'}.
#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed bootleg walker'}.
#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed tesla walker'}.
#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed fusion walker'}.
#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed buckshot walker'}.
#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed flare walker'}.
#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed laser walker'}.
#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed flamer walker'}.
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "You misprogram the walker; it's IFF identifies you as hostile!"
msgstr "你错误编程了步行机；它的敌我识别系统将你标记为敌对目标！"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed chicken walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An Northrup ATSV, packed for transport.  Armed with a 5.56 anti-personnel "
"rifle, an anti-vehicle 40mm grenade launcher and a tazer.  Use this item to "
"unpack and load with up to 1000 5.56 NATO M855A1 and 50 40mm frag rounds."
msgstr ""
"一台诺斯罗普ATSV，已打包以便运输。装备有一把5.56毫米反人员步枪、一门40毫米反车辆榴弹发射器和一支电击枪。使用此物品可解包并装载最多1000发5.56"
" NATO M855A1子弹和50发40毫米破片榴弹。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed scrap walker"
msgid_plural "packed scrap walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的废料步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed scrap walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A severely damaged Northrup ATSV, packed for transport.  Armed with a 5.56 "
"anti-personnel rifle, an anti-vehicle 40mm grenade launcher and a tazer.  "
"Use this item to unpack and load with up to 220 5.56 NATO M855A1 and 12 40mm"
" frag rounds."
msgstr ""
"一台严重损坏的诺斯罗普ATSV，已打包以便运输。装备有一把5.56毫米反人员步枪、一门40毫米反车辆榴弹发射器和一支电击枪。使用此物品可解包并装载最多220发5.56"
" NATO M855A1子弹和12发40毫米破片榴弹。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed unarmed walker"
msgid_plural "packed unarmed walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的无武装步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed unarmed walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap, packed for transport.  Armed "
"with a only a tazer, it is ineffective in combat, and really should have "
"some weapons installed before activation."
msgstr "一台由废料拼凑而成的诺斯罗普ATSV，已打包以便运输。仅装备一支电击枪，在战斗中效果不佳，激活前确实应安装一些武器。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed unarmed super walker"
msgid_plural "packed unarmed super walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的无武装超级步行机"

#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed unarmed super walker'}.
#. ~ Use action friendly_msg for {'str': 'packed super walker'}.
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "You hear \"STARTUP CHECKLIST COMPLETE.  ALL SYSTEMS GREEN.\""
msgstr "你听到“启动检查清单完成。所有系统正常。”"

#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed unarmed super walker'}.
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "You misprogram the walker! Embrace Deus Machina's purification!"
msgstr "你错误编程了步行机！迎接机械之神的净化吧！"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed unarmed super walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A large combat walker based on the Northrup ATSV, packed for transport.  "
"Though it is armed with electroshock and -magnet units alongside "
"mechadendrite-mounted blades, you really should install its primary weapon "
"systems before activation."
msgstr ""
"一台基于诺斯罗普ATSV的大型战斗步行机，已打包以便运输。尽管它装备有电击和电磁单元以及机械触手安装的刀刃，但在激活前你确实应安装其主要武器系统。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed super walker"
msgid_plural "packed super walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的超级步行机"

#. ~ Use action hostile_msg for {'str': 'packed super walker'}.
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "You misprogram the walker.  Oops."
msgstr "你错误编程了步行机。哎呀。"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed super walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A large combat walker based on the Northrup ATSV, packed for transport.  "
"Armed with an M2 Browning .50 calibre machine gun, electroshock and -magnet "
"units alongside six mechadendrite-mounted blades.  Use this item to unpack "
"and load with up to 1000 .50 BMG Ball rounds."
msgstr ""
"一台基于诺斯罗普ATSV的大型战斗步行机，已打包以便运输。装备有一挺M2勃朗宁.50口径机枪、电击和电磁单元以及六把机械触手安装的刀刃。使用此物品可解包并装载最多1000发.50"
" BMG普通弹。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed bootleg walker"
msgid_plural "packed bootleg walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的山寨步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed bootleg walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An inactive bootleg walker, packed for transport.  Armed with a pair of 5.56"
" anti-personnel rifles and a tazer.  Use this item to unpack and load with "
"up to 1000 5.56 NATO M855A1 rounds."
msgstr ""
"一台未激活的山寨步行机，已打包以便运输。装备有两把5.56毫米反人员步枪和一支电击枪。使用此物品可解包并装载最多1000发5.56 NATO "
"M855A1子弹。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed tesla walker"
msgid_plural "packed tesla walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的特斯拉步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed tesla walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An inactive tesla walker, packed for transport.  Armed with a pair of "
"powerful tesla coils and a tazer.  Use this item to unpack."
msgstr "一台未激活的特斯拉步行机，已打包以便运输。装备有两台强大的特斯拉线圈和一支电击枪。使用此物品可解包。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed fusion walker"
msgid_plural "packed fusion walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的聚变步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed fusion walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An inactive fusion walker, packed for transport.  Armed with a pair of "
"fusion blasters and a tazer.  Use this item to unpack."
msgstr "一台未激活的聚变步行机，已打包以便运输。装备有两门聚变冲击炮和一支电击枪。使用此物品可解包。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed buckshot walker"
msgid_plural "packed buckshot walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的霰弹步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed buckshot walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An inactive buckshot walker, packed for transport.  Armed with a pair of "
"automatic shotguns and a tazer.  Use this item to unpack and load with up to"
" 500 00 shot."
msgstr "一台未激活的霰弹步行机，已打包以便运输。装备有两把自动霰弹枪和一支电击枪。使用此物品可解包并装载最多500发00号霰弹。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed flare walker"
msgid_plural "packed flare walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的信号弹步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed flare walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An inactive flare walker, packed for transport.  Equipped with a flare "
"launcher.  Use this item to unpack and load with up to 500 signal flares."
msgstr "一个处于非活动状态的信号弹步行者，已打包以便运输。装备有信号弹发射器。使用此物品可解包并装载最多500发信号弹。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed laser walker"
msgid_plural "packed laser walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的激光步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed laser walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An inactive laser walker, packed for transport.  Armed with a trio of lasers"
" and a tazer.  Use this item to unpack."
msgstr "一个处于非活动状态的激光步行者，已打包以便运输。配备了三门激光炮和一个电击枪。使用此物品可解包。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "packed flamer walker"
msgid_plural "packed flamer walkers"
msgstr[0] "打包的喷火步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'packed flamer walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"An inactive flamer walker, packed for transport.  Armed with a heavy "
"flamethrower and a tazer.  Use this item to unpack and fuel with up to 10 "
"litres of napalm."
msgstr "一个处于非活动状态的喷火步行者，已打包以便运输。配备了一台重型火焰喷射器和一个电击枪。使用此物品可解包并装载最多10升凝固汽油。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken unarmed super walker"
msgid_plural "broken unarmed super walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的无武装超级步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken unarmed super walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken unarmed super walker.  Even without its gun, this was a force to be"
" reckoned with.  What could have done this?  Still, you may be able to "
"reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的无武装超级步行者。即使没有枪，它也曾是一股不可小觑的力量。是什么造成了这一切？不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken unarmed walker"
msgid_plural "broken unarmed walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的无武装步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken unarmed walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken unarmed walker.  Proof that refraining from installing weaponry was"
" foolish.  Still, you may be able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的无武装步行者。这证明了不安装武器是愚蠢的。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken super walker"
msgid_plural "broken super walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的超级步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken super walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken super walker.  What terrors could possibly do such a thing?  You "
"shudder to think of the possibilities.  Still, you may be able to reclaim "
"parts from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的超级步行者。什么样的恐怖存在能做出这种事？光是想想可能性就让你不寒而栗。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken flamer walker"
msgid_plural "broken flamer walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的喷火步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken flamer walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken flamer walker.  Its lust for chaos has been extinguished.  Still, "
"you may be able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的喷火步行者。它对混乱的渴望已被熄灭。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken laser walker"
msgid_plural "broken laser walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的激光步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken laser walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken laser walker.  No longer shall you hear the snap of superheated "
"air, smell the burning of flesh.  Still, you may be able to reclaim parts "
"from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的激光步行者。你将不再听到过热空气的爆裂声，不再闻到肉体烧焦的气味。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken bootleg walker"
msgid_plural "broken bootleg walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的仿制步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken bootleg walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken bootleg walker.  Its guns are quiet now.  Still, you may be able to"
" reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的仿制步行者。它的枪炮如今已归于沉寂。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken flare walker"
msgid_plural "broken flare walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的信号弹步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken flare walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken flare walker.  Its flares shall remain dark, forevermore.  Still, "
"you may be able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的信号弹步行者。它的信号弹将永远黯淡无光。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken tesla walker"
msgid_plural "broken tesla walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的特斯拉步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken tesla walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken tesla walker.  The dance of lightning has ceased.  Still, you may "
"be able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的特斯拉步行者。闪电之舞已然停歇。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken fusion walker"
msgid_plural "broken fusion walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的聚变步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken fusion walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken fusion walker.  City and forest need not fear its wrath any longer."
"  Still, you may be able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的聚变步行者。城市与森林无需再畏惧它的怒火。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken buckshot walker"
msgid_plural "broken buckshot walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的霰弹步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken buckshot walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken buckshot walker.  Deer and duck alike rejoice.  Still, you may be "
"able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的霰弹步行者。鹿与鸭都为此欢欣鼓舞。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken chicken walker"
msgid_plural "broken chicken walkers"
msgstr[0] "损坏的鸡型步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken chicken walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken Northrup ATSV.  It lays quiet now, though looking upon it brings "
"memories of fire and death.  Still, you may be able to reclaim parts from "
"the wreck."
msgstr "一个损坏的诺斯罗普ATSV。它如今静静地躺着，但凝视它时，仍会唤起关于火焰与死亡的记忆。不过，你或许能从残骸中回收一些零件。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "chicken walker"
msgid_plural "chicken walkers"
msgstr[0] "鸡形步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'chicken walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"The Northrop ATSV, a massive, heavily-armed and armored robot walking on a "
"pair of reverse-jointed legs.  Armed with a 40mm anti-vehicle grenade "
"launcher, 5.56 anti-personnel gun, and the ability to electrify itself "
"against attackers, it is an effective automated sentry, though production "
"was limited due to a legal dispute."
msgstr ""
"诺斯罗普ATSV，一种庞大、重武装且重装甲的机器人，以一对反关节腿行走。配备40毫米反车辆榴弹发射器、5.56毫米反人员枪械，并能对攻击者释放电击，是一种高效的自动哨兵，但因法律纠纷生产受限。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "scrap walker"
msgid_plural "scrap walkers"
msgstr[0] "废料步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'scrap walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"The Northrup ATSV, a massive, heavily-armed and armored robot walking on a "
"pair of reverse-jointed legs.  Armed with a 40mm anti-vehicle grenade "
"launcher, 5.56 anti-personnel gun, and the ability to electrify itself "
"against attackers, it is an effective automated sentry.  Or would be, if it "
"wasn't held together with duct tape and hope."
msgstr ""
"诺斯罗普ATSV，一个巨大的、全副武装的重型机器人，依靠一对反关节腿行走。装备有40毫米反车辆榴弹发射器、5.56毫米反人员机枪，并能对攻击者进行电击自卫，是一款高效的自动哨兵。或者说，如果它不是靠胶带和希望勉强拼凑起来的话，本该如此。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "super walker"
msgid_plural "super walkers"
msgstr[0] "超级步行者"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'super walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A large combat walker based on the Northrup ATSV.  Armed with an M2 Browning"
" .50 calibre machine gun, electroshock and -magnet units alongside six "
"mechadendrite-mounted blades.  Features  improved combat logic, thick "
"superalloy-ceramic composite plating, enhanced optics, motors and sensors "
"and an offensive defence system ."
msgstr ""
"一款基于诺斯罗普ATSV的大型战斗步行机。装备有M2勃朗宁.50口径机枪、电击与磁力单元，以及六把机械触手搭载的刀刃。具备改进的战斗逻辑、厚重的超级合金-"
"陶瓷复合装甲、增强的光学设备、马达与传感器，以及一套进攻性防御系统。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "unarmed super walker"
msgid_plural "unarmed super walkers"
msgstr[0] "未武装超级步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'unarmed super walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A large combat walker based on the Northrup ATSV.  Though it is armed with "
"electroshock and -magnet units alongside mechadendrite-mounted blades, you "
"really should deactivate it to install its primary weapon systems."
msgstr "一款基于诺斯罗普ATSV的大型战斗步行机。虽然装备有电击与磁力单元以及机械触手搭载的刀刃，但你真的应该先停用它，以便安装其主要武器系统。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "unarmed walker"
msgid_plural "unarmed walkers"
msgstr[0] "未武装步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'unarmed walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a only a tazer, it "
"is ineffective in combat, and really should be deactivated for weapon "
"installation."
msgstr "一款用废料拼凑而成的诺斯罗普ATSV。仅装备一把泰瑟枪，在战斗中效果不佳，确实应该停用以安装武器。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "bootleg walker"
msgid_plural "bootleg walkers"
msgstr[0] "山寨步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'bootleg walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a pair of 5.56 "
"rifles, it is quite deadly.  Still, you shouldn't expect the reliability and"
" resilience of the real thing."
msgstr "一款用废料拼凑而成的诺斯罗普ATSV。装备两把5.56毫米步枪，相当致命。不过，你别指望它能像正品那样可靠耐用。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "buckshot walker"
msgid_plural "buckshot walkers"
msgstr[0] "霰弹步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'buckshot walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a pair of automatic"
" shotguns, it is quite deadly.  Still, you shouldn't expect the reliability "
"and resilience of the real thing."
msgstr "一款用废料拼凑而成的诺斯罗普ATSV。装备两把自动霰弹枪，相当致命。不过，你别指望它能像正品那样可靠耐用。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "flare walker"
msgid_plural "flare walkers"
msgstr[0] "信号弹步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'flare walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Equipped with a flaregun and "
"tazer, it functions as a spotter for more lethal models.  Still, you "
"shouldn't expect the reliability and resilience of the real thing."
msgstr "一款用废料拼凑而成的诺斯罗普ATSV。装备信号枪和泰瑟枪，作为更致命型号的侦察单位使用。不过，你别指望它能像正品那样可靠耐用。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "laser walker"
msgid_plural "laser walkers"
msgstr[0] "激光步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'laser walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a trio of lasers, "
"it is fairly deadly.  Still, you shouldn't expect the reliability and "
"resilience of the real thing."
msgstr "一款用废料拼凑而成的诺斯罗普ATSV。装备三把激光枪，相当致命。不过，你别指望它能像正品那样可靠耐用。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "fusion walker"
msgid_plural "fusion walkers"
msgstr[0] "聚变步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'fusion walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a pair of fusion "
"blasters, it is extremely deadly.  Still, you shouldn't expect the "
"reliability and resilience of the real thing."
msgstr "一款用废料拼凑而成的诺斯罗普ATSV。装备两把聚变冲击炮，极其致命。不过，你别指望它能像正品那样可靠耐用。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "tesla walker"
msgid_plural "tesla walkers"
msgstr[0] "特斯拉步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'tesla walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a pair of tesla "
"coils, it is fairly deadly.  Still, you shouldn't expect the reliability and"
" resilience of the real thing, and it may be damaged by it's own lightning."
msgstr "一款用废料拼凑而成的诺斯罗普ATSV。装备两套特斯拉线圈，相当致命。不过，你别指望它能像正品那样可靠耐用，而且它可能会被自己的闪电损坏。"

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "flamer walker"
msgid_plural "flamer walkers"
msgstr[0] "喷火步行机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'flamer walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a heavy "
"flamethrower, it is extremely deadly.  Still, you shouldn't expect the "
"reliability and resilience of the real thing."
msgstr "一款用废料拼凑而成的诺斯罗普ATSV。装备一把重型火焰喷射器，极其致命。不过，你别指望它能像正品那样可靠耐用。"
